#: ../../D/dangling-pointer.rst:5
msgid "dangling pointer"
msgstr "dangling pointer"

#: ../../D/dangling-pointer.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../D/dangling-pointer.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] A reference that doesn't actually lead anywhere (in C and some "
"other languages, a pointer that doesn't actually point at anything valid). "
"Usually this happens because it formerly pointed to something that has moved"
" or disappeared. Used as jargon in a generalization of its techspeak "
"meaning; for example, a local phone number for a person who has since moved "
"to the other coast is a dangling pointer."
msgstr ""
"[一般的] "
"実際にはどこにもつながっていない参照(Cや他のいくつかの言語では、実際には有効な何物も指していないポインタ)。通常これは、かつて指していた何かが移動したか消えたために起こる。専門用語的な意味を一般化した俗語として使われる。たとえば、その後反対の海岸に引っ越した人の地元の電話番号は、dangling"
" pointerである。"
